      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While automation and demographics are real challenges, the primary driver of declining labor participation over the last decade is the structural design of the social safety net itself. When benefits are structured to be so generous that they exceed the earnings of low-wage jobs, they actively discourage people from seeking employment, creating a direct disincentive that no amount of technological change can fix. Ignoring this specific policy failure in favor of blaming external factors like automation is a distraction from the fact that we are actively engineering a workforce that refuses to work because the government has made it too profitable to stay home.",
